    5) -B 	: working perfectly
    6) -P 	: working perfectly
Trace output :
    1) regular packets: working perfectly
    2) dropped packets: working perfectly
    3) removed packets: working perfectly
    4) token arrival (dropped or not dropped): working perfectly
Statistics output :
    1) inter-arrival time 			: working perfectly
    2) service time 				: working perfectly
    3) number of customers in Q1 		: working perfectly
    4) number of customers in Q2		: working perfectly
    5) number of customers at a server 		: working perfectly
    6) time in system 				: working perfectly
    7) standard deviation for time in system 	: working perfectly
    8) drop probability 			: working perfectly

Output bad format 							 : working perfectly
Output wrong precision for statistics (should be 6-8 significant digits) : statictics are being printed correctly as specified
Large service time test						: working perfectly
Large inter-arrival time test 					: working perfectly
Tiny inter-arrival time test 					: working perfectly
Tiny service time test 						: working perfectly
Large total number of customers test 				: working perfectly
